OL,3,CMountain rescuer paid 'ultimate price'
OL,4,Cfor lockdown callout, inquest finds
OL,6,FA coroner has concluded that mountain
OL,7,Frescue volunteer Chris Lewis paid the
OL,8,F"ultimate price" when he was called
OL,9,Fout to help two men who broke lockdown
OL,10,Frules.
OL,12,FChris was volunteering with when he
OL,13,Ffell almost 500ft down the steep face
OL,14,Fof Red Screes, above Kirkstone Pass in
OL,15,Fthe Lake District.
OL,17,FThe coroner recorded an accidental
OL,18,Fdeath, despite a 31 month gap between
OL,19,Fthe accident and his death, she
OL,20,Fconcluded that it was as a result of
OL,21,Fthat fall.
