OL,6,FShe said that while nobody could say
OL,7,Fwith any certainty what caused his
OL,8,Ffall, as no one witnessed the
OL,9,Fincident, she could be satisfied he
OL,10,Fdid not intend to do so.
OL,12,FHe died of pneumonia and a serious
OL,13,Ftraumatic spinal injury sustained
OL,14,Fduring the rescue.
OL,16,FHis wife Carol told the inquest how
OL,17,FChris loved the outdoors, describing
OL,18,Fhim as a very active man, who joined
OL,19,Fthe team when he retired.
