OL,6,FThe coroner Kirsty Gomersal said,
OL,7,FChris "paid the ultimate price,"
OL,8,Fadding that his injuries were
OL,9,Fsustained as a result of his
OL,10,F"selflessness".
OL,12,FShe also paid tribute to other
OL,13,Fmountain rescuers and volunteers who
OL,14,Fgive their time and skills to serve
OL,15,Fthose who find themselves in distress.
OL,17,FChris Lewis, who lived near , died
OL,18,Fpeacefully with his wife at his side,
OL,19,F31 months after he sustained life
OL,20,Fchanging injuries during a rescue in
OL,21,Fthe early hours of 6th February 2021.
